<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tbarticle" summary="article">
<tr class="txttop">

<td>NOW ON TEST<br />
<br />
"The LDoN raids have been switched over from the old adventure system to the expedition system.<br />
<br />
The major benefits to this include:<br />
Being able to add new players at any point during the raid<br />
The lockout for the raid occurs at the end after a success instead of the beginning<br />
<br />
In addition, the player maximum has been increased from 36 to 54, and all death counter failure mechanics have been removed from the raids.<br />
<br />
These changes are currently on Beta and Test.<br />
<br />
There is the possibility that something important slipped through the cracks when switching the system over. If you've done the LDoN raids before and have any questions or feedback, or even if you haven't, let me know.<br />
<br />
Thanks!<br />
-Prathun"<br />
<br />
Also:<br />
"Is the requirment of two wins at the camps for each player still tied into being added to the raid?"<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
<br />
"Oh, good question. <br />
The requirement for two wins at a camp to launch an associated raid was pretty minor. It didn't add much to gameplay and I'm not interested in adding more barriers of entry to content that's already underused. No two win requirement."<br />
<br />
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
<br />
There's also some nice +spellcasting specialization% modifiers (10 or 15%) and some very nice AC augments available as well from these.  With luck we'll see more people doing these raids. <br />
<br />
<br />
Link to thread:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=227425#M227425" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq...=227425#M227425</a></td>
</tr>
